The paper deals with the analysis of the behavior of the outage probability in cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a new concept, the asymptotic deployment gain (ADG), which characterizes the performance of different point processes in the high-reliability regime, which is a topic related to mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses simulations to investigate the outage probabilities and ADGs for different point processes and fading statistics, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT).
